                                    </figure>
                                    <p>To solve the equation <m>\abs{\frac{2}{3}x+2}=4</m>, we will make a graph with both <m>y=\abs{\frac{2}{3}x+2}</m> and <m>y=4</m>. The solution set is <m>\{-9,3\}</m>.</p>
