                                    </figure>
                                    <p>To solve the inequality <m>\abs{\frac{2}{3}x+2}\gt 4</m>, we will make a graph with both <m>y=\abs{\frac{2}{3}x+2}</m> and <m>y=4</m>. We have highlighted the solution region that lies above <m>y=4</m>. The solution set is <m>(-\infty,-9)\cup(3,\infty)</m>.</p>
                                </sidebyside>
                            </li>
                            <li>  
